@@IJvSpellChecker.OnCanIgnore
Summary
  Event handler that is called for every word in the text.
Description
  Write a handler for the OnCanIgnore event when you need to set up ignores for words that can't be
  easily captured using a simple table driven spell checker. For example, to ignore upper case words,
  you could write an event handler that compares the current word with its upper cased variant and
  set CanIgnore to true if they match.
Parameters
  Sender    - The IJvSpellChecker implementor
  Value     - The string to check.
  CanIgnore - Set to true to skip the word, false to handle it normally.

